          <p><strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong></p>
<p><em>What is the exposure for an existing Vault cluster?</em></p>
<p>Vault-issued tokens with non-expiring leases created as a result of this issue do not present security risk, as Vault does not accept those tokens as valid.</p>
<p>Vault-issued dynamic secrets with non-expiring leases created as a result of this issue <strong>do</strong> present security risk, as Vault will not have revoked those from the associated secrets engine and these secrets may be accepted as valid by the underlying service.</p>
<p><em>How can tokens with non-expiring leases be identified and revoked?</em></p>
<p>The attached script may be used to list these tokens. Vault’s <a href="https://www.vaultproject.io/docs/commands/token/revoke">token revoke</a> command is not effective against these tokens, as Vault does not accept these tokens as valid.</p>
<p>As noted in the bulletin, Vault and Vault Enterprise 1.5.9 / 1.6.5 / 1.7.2 or newer will automatically expire / revoke any non-expiring tokens that exist as a result of this issue.</p>
<p><a class="attachment" href="/uploads/short-url/dQr3iki1br2n0Vp014ieFkSQcaQ.sh">hcsec-2021-15-list-nonexpiring-tokens.sh</a> (1022 Bytes)</p>
<p><em>How can dynamic secrets with non-expiring leases be identified and revoked?</em></p>
<p>The attached script may be used to list these dynamic secrets, and Vault’s <a href="https://www.vaultproject.io/docs/commands/lease/revoke">lease revoke</a> command can then be used to trigger revocation by the Vault secrets engine and underlying service.</p>
<p>As noted in the bulletin, Vault and Vault Enterprise 1.5.9 / 1.6.5 / 1.7.2 or newer will automatically expire / revoke any non-expiring dynamic secrets that exist as a result of this issue.</p>
<p><a class="attachment" href="/uploads/short-url/vCxRSWnzgyU0iDrtKmidnidAt5K.sh">hcsec-2021-15-list-nonexpiring-leases.sh</a> (1.5 KB)</p>
